wikipedia_page.main: Patrick Philbin (4 August 1874 in Castlebar, Co. Mayo, Ireland – 1929) was a British tug of war competitor who competed in the 1908 Summer Olympics. In 1908 he won the silver medal as member of the British team Liverpool Police.
